<text top="121" left="120" width="22" height="14" font="26"><b>1.0 </b></text>
<text top="121" left="195" width="80" height="14" font="26"><b>GENERAL </b></text>
<text top="157" left="119" width="21" height="14" font="26"><b>1.1 </b></text>
<text top="157" left="195" width="566" height="14" font="22">This specification provides instructions for the laying of Fire Bricks in fired heaters, using </text>
<text top="175" left="195" width="566" height="14" font="22">air setting mortar. It is also applicable for laying of bricks for firewalls &amp; bridge walls in </text>
<text top="193" left="195" width="84" height="14" font="22">fired heaters. </text>
<text top="231" left="119" width="21" height="14" font="26"><b>1.2 </b></text>
<text top="231" left="195" width="567" height="14" font="22">The success of brick lining depends to a large extent on correct execution at site. It is </text>
<text top="249" left="195" width="566" height="14" font="22">therefore imperative that the instructions provided herein are exactly followed. EIL </text>
<text top="267" left="195" width="566" height="14" font="22">refractory specialist shall be consulted whenever it shall be considered requisite by the </text>
<text top="285" left="196" width="130" height="14" font="22">Engineer-in-Charge. </text>
<text top="324" left="119" width="22" height="14" font="26"><b>1.3 </b></text>
<text top="324" left="195" width="566" height="14" font="22">The lining work shall be carried out as per approved lining drawings and procedure by ELL </text>
<text top="342" left="195" width="162" height="14" font="22">/ PMC approved Agency. </text>
<text top="380" left="119" width="22" height="14" font="26"><b>1.4 </b></text>
<text top="381" left="194" width="470" height="14" font="22">The Lining Agency shall obtain permission from EIC before start of lining. </text>
<text top="418" left="118" width="23" height="14" font="22">2.0 </text>
<text top="419" left="195" width="315" height="14" font="26"><b>ANCHORING SYSTEM FOR BRICK WORK </b></text>
<text top="457" left="118" width="23" height="14" font="22">2.1 </text>
<text top="458" left="195" width="566" height="14" font="22">All brick linings on vertical flat casing shall be tied back to, and supported by the structural </text>
<text top="476" left="194" width="568" height="14" font="22">steel framing members. Brick work may not require to be tied back in case the radius of </text>
<text top="494" left="194" width="567" height="14" font="22">curvature of the wall is low enough to key-in the bricks. For flat walls, at least 20% of the </text>
<text top="512" left="195" width="566" height="14" font="22">brick shall be tied back. Tie back shall extend into at least 1/3rd the thickness of the hot face </text>
<text top="529" left="195" width="38" height="14" font="22">layer. </text>
<text top="567" left="117" width="23" height="14" font="22">2.2 </text>
<text top="568" left="194" width="567" height="14" font="22">Sectional supports, if any, in the form of shelf flats / lintels shall be provided along the </text>
<text top="586" left="195" width="566" height="14" font="22">height as per the arrangement drawing. The purpose of shelf flats is to reduce the cumulative </text>
<text top="603" left="194" width="499" height="14" font="22">vertical expansion and to minimize maintenance in the event of localized repair. </text>
<text top="642" left="195" width="567" height="14" font="22">Unless otherwise noted in arrangement drawing, MOC of shelf plate shall be SS310. </text>
<text top="660" left="194" width="567" height="14" font="22">Support shelves shall be slotted to take care of differential thermal expansion. Support </text>
<text top="678" left="194" width="567" height="14" font="22">shelves shall be regularly spaced vertically at approximate pitch of 1.8 meter. Vertical pitch </text>
<text top="696" left="194" width="568" height="14" font="22">of support shelves shall be calculated based on load &amp; thermal expansion and shall not </text>
<text top="714" left="194" width="113" height="14" font="22">exceed 3.0 meter. </text>
<text top="752" left="117" width="23" height="14" font="26"><b>2.3 </b></text>
<text top="752" left="194" width="567" height="14" font="22">Horizontal Flats with holes for brick holding style shall be welded to the casing in each </text>
<text top="770" left="194" width="500" height="14" font="22">panel as per the arrangement drawing. Material construction shall be as follows: </text>
<text top="809" left="193" width="67" height="14" font="26"><b>a)  Flats: </b></text>
<text top="847" left="218" width="543" height="14" font="22">Flats can be of CS material in case it is confined to the non-brick backup insulation layer </text>
<text top="865" left="217" width="544" height="14" font="22">and the calculated design temperature is limited to 370 °C. However, as a minimum the </text>
<text top="883" left="218" width="383" height="14" font="22">MOC indicated in the arrangement drawing shall be adopted. </text>
<text top="922" left="194" width="191" height="14" font="26"><b>b)  Vertical Cleat Supports: </b></text>
<text top="960" left="217" width="544" height="14" font="22">In case of vertical cleat supports where the cleat height is more than the depth of backup </text>
<text top="978" left="217" width="499" height="14" font="22">insulation, the MOC of cleats shall be SS310 UON in the arrangement drawing. </text>
<text top="1013" left="117" width="23" height="14" font="26"><b>2.4 </b></text>
<text top="1014" left="193" width="567" height="14" font="22">The staples are normally made from 5mm dia. rods of SS310H to ASTM A479 Gr. 310H / </text>
<text top="1032" left="193" width="263" height="14" font="22">equivalent VON in arrangement drawing. </text>
<text top="1070" left="116" width="24" height="14" font="26"><b>3.0 </b></text>
<text top="1070" left="194" width="192" height="14" font="26"><b>PRELINING INSPECTION </b></text>
<text top="1109" left="116" width="23" height="14" font="26"><b>3.1 </b></text>
<text top="1109" left="194" width="568" height="14" font="22">Prior to installation a thorough inspection shall be carried out for readiness for brick lining. </text>
<text top="1142" left="586" width="174" height="10" font="0">Copyright EIL — All rights reserved </text>
<text top="1145" left="116" width="168" height="10" font="0">Format No. 8-00-0001-F1 Rev. 0 </text>
</page>
<page number="5" position="absolute" top="0" left="0" height="1260" width="895">
	<fontspec id="27" size="15" family="Times" color="#000000"/>
	<fontspec id="28" size="17" family="Times" color="#000000"/>
	<fontspec id="29" size="6" family="Helvetica" color="#000000"/>
	<fontspec id="30" size="15" family="Times" color="#000000"/>
<text top="351" left="2063" width="9" height="12" font="16"> </text>
<text top="351" left="2744" width="9" height="12" font="16"> </text>
<text top="351" left="3980" width="9" height="12" font="16"> </text>
<text top="54" left="229" width="73" height="13" font="27">ENGINEERS </text>
<text top="48" left="348" width="228" height="12" font="2">STANDARD SPECIFICATION FOR </text>
<text top="68" left="228" width="43" height="12" font="2">INDIA </text>
<text top="68" left="270" width="55" height="14" font="27">LIMITED </text>
<text top="64" left="347" width="230" height="12" font="2">INSTALLATION OF BRICK LINING </text>
<text top="82" left="229" width="8" height="6" font="24">(4 </text>
<text top="82" left="254" width="7" height="6" font="24">ol </text>
<text top="82" left="276" width="38" height="6" font="24">Unoertaking, </text>
<text top="81" left="394" width="135" height="12" font="2">IN FIRED HEATERS </text>
<text top="48" left="606" width="178" height="10" font="0">STANDARD SPECIFICATION No. </text>
<text top="68" left="638" width="113" height="12" font="2">6-17-0011 Rev. 2 </text>
<text top="87" left="664" width="61" height="10" font="0">Page 5 of 7 </text>
<text top="67" left="115" width="87" height="16" font="28"><b>zige_4116i5reg </b></text>
<text top="81" left="134" width="65" height="6" font="29"><b>1•402P1 IK,WIF ,RWA </b></text>
<text top="120" left="116" width="24" height="14" font="27">3.2 </text>
<text top="121" left="193" width="565" height="14" font="27">Check that the MOC and installation of all the items used in the anchoring system as defined </text>
<text top="139" left="194" width="565" height="14" font="27">in Clause 2.0 above are in accordance with the approved drawings. Horizontal flats with </text>
<text top="157" left="194" width="565" height="14" font="27">holes or vertical cleats with slotted holes should be available on the casing for holding the </text>
<text top="175" left="193" width="565" height="14" font="27">brick staples. Sectional supports in the form of shelf flats / lintels should be available for </text>
<text top="193" left="193" width="231" height="14" font="27">supporting the base course of bricks. </text>
<text top="231" left="116" width="25" height="14" font="27">3.3 </text>
<text top="231" left="194" width="564" height="14" font="27">In case of brick lining with back-up layer, the back- up layer should have been installed in </text>
<text top="249" left="193" width="57" height="14" font="27">position. </text>
<text top="288" left="116" width="24" height="14" font="27">3.4 </text>
<text top="288" left="193" width="565" height="14" font="27">There should be no undulations in the surface to be lined. The undulations can be the result </text>
<text top="306" left="193" width="486" height="14" font="27">of distortion in the casing or local bulges due to poor quality of backup lining. </text>
<text top="344" left="116" width="25" height="14" font="27">3.5 </text>
<text top="344" left="193" width="566" height="14" font="27">The floor casing and the shelf flats which would seat the base course of bricks should also </text>
<text top="362" left="193" width="328" height="14" font="27">be checked for proper integrity, level and alignment. </text>
<text top="401" left="115" width="25" height="14" font="27">3.6 </text>
<text top="401" left="193" width="566" height="14" font="27">The condition and cleanliness of the surfaces to be lined shall be checked. The surfaces to </text>
<text top="419" left="192" width="567" height="14" font="27">come in contact with brick lining shall be cleaned to remove any dirt, grit, loose scale or </text>
<text top="437" left="192" width="143" height="14" font="27">other foreign material. </text>
<text top="475" left="115" width="25" height="14" font="27">3.7 </text>
<text top="475" left="193" width="566" height="14" font="27">For equipment to be brick-lined, the temperature of the wet mix of mortar shall be </text>
<text top="493" left="193" width="566" height="14" font="27">maintained between 5-38°C. In case stringent requirement is specified by manufacturer, the </text>
<text top="511" left="192" width="150" height="14" font="27">same shall be followed. </text>
<text top="550" left="115" width="25" height="14" font="27">3.8 </text>
<text top="550" left="193" width="566" height="14" font="27">In case of cylindrical surface 'Key' brick shall be inserted in full dimension, if required the </text>
<text top="568" left="192" width="434" height="14" font="27">adjacent brick may be cut to suit (not less than the 50% of the width). </text>
<text top="606" left="116" width="24" height="14" font="30"><b>4.0 </b></text>
<text top="606" left="193" width="97" height="14" font="30"><b>MATERIALS </b></text>
<text top="644" left="116" width="23" height="14" font="30"><b>4.1 </b></text>
<text top="645" left="193" width="566" height="14" font="27">Materials shall be stored in original packaging as per supplier recommendations and shall </text>
<text top="662" left="192" width="337" height="14" font="27">be protected from moisture and foreign contaminants. </text>
<text top="700" left="115" width="23" height="14" font="30"><b>4.2 </b></text>
<text top="701" left="193" width="566" height="14" font="27">Bricks used shall be free from cracks, chips, broken edges / corners, spalling or other </text>
<text top="719" left="192" width="567" height="14" font="27">defects. Bricks shall be evenly fired and of uniform color. Old bricks shall not be reclaimed </text>
<text top="737" left="192" width="62" height="14" font="27">and used. </text>
<text top="775" left="116" width="24" height="14" font="27">4.3 </text>
<text top="775" left="192" width="567" height="14" font="27">The mortar used for brick lining shall be non-slagging, air setting, chemically compatible </text>
<text top="793" left="192" width="443" height="14" font="27">with adjacent refractory and suitable for the rated temperature of brick. </text>
<text top="832" left="196" width="540" height="14" font="27">Mortar used for jointing bridge wall bricks shall meet the following additional criteria: </text>
<text top="870" left="198" width="13" height="14" font="27">I. </text>
<text top="870" left="235" width="444" height="14" font="27">Shall be suitable for continuous operating temperature of —1000°C min </text>
<text top="909" left="195" width="16" height="14" font="27">2. </text>
<text top="909" left="236" width="373" height="14" font="27">It should not contain any fluxing material like sodium silica </text>
<text top="947" left="196" width="271" height="14" font="27">Mortar used should be within the shelf life. </text>
<text top="986" left="115" width="24" height="14" font="30"><b>4.4 </b></text>
<text top="986" left="192" width="347" height="14" font="27">Air setting mortars are normally supplied in two forms: </text>
<text top="1022" left="191" width="141" height="14" font="30"><b>a) Two Component </b></text>
<text top="1022" left="331" width="56" height="12" font="2">System: </text>
<text top="1058" left="218" width="542" height="14" font="27">In the two-component system, powder is supplied in bags and liquid binders are </text>
<text top="1076" left="216" width="544" height="14" font="27">supplied in containers which are mixed at site prior to installation. This system is </text>
<text top="1094" left="217" width="252" height="14" font="27">normally preferred for bonding of IFBs. </text>
<text top="1141" left="584" width="175" height="10" font="0">Copyright EIL — All rights reserved </text>
<text top="1144" left="115" width="167" height="10" font="0">Format No. 8-00-0001-F1 Rev. 0 </text>
</page>
<page number="6" position="absolute" top="0" left="0" height="1260" width="895">
	<fontspec id="31" size="16" family="Helvetica" color="#000000"/>
	<fontspec id="32" size="18" family="Helvetica" color="#000000"/>
<text top="55" left="143" width="13" height="13" font="2">ks--</text>
<text top="53" left="152" width="52" height="15" font="31">ilf-a.it4 </text>
<text top="48" left="348" width="227" height="13" font="1"><b>STANDARD SPECIFICATION FOR </b></text>
<text top="64" left="346" width="230" height="13" font="1"><b>INSTALLATION OF BRICK LINING </b></text>
<text top="81" left="393" width="134" height="13" font="1"><b>IN FIRED HEATERS </b></text>
<text top="48" left="605" width="178" height="10" font="0">STANDARD SPECIFICATION No. </text>
<text top="67" left="637" width="113" height="13" font="1"><b>6-17-0011 Rev. 2 </b></text>
<text top="87" left="663" width="60" height="10" font="0">Page 6 of 7 </text>
<text top="55" left="228" width="74" height="13" font="27">ENGINEERS </text>
<text top="66" left="107" width="45" height="17" font="20">lfgar </text>
<text top="67" left="148" width="55" height="17" font="32">fEtit&amp;g </text>
<text top="67" left="198" width="1" height="17" font="20"> </text>
<text top="83" left="150" width="23" height="5" font="3">ritant </text>
<text top="68" left="228" width="97" height="14" font="27">INDIA LIMITED </text>
<text top="84" left="227" width="86" height="5" font="3">IA Goo of InOta Uncleftdiong, </text>
<text top="122" left="192" width="207" height="13" font="1"><b>b) Single Component System: </b></text>
<text top="160" left="216" width="541" height="14" font="27">This is supplied in powder form to which requisite amount of water is added as </text>
<text top="178" left="217" width="540" height="14" font="27">recommended by the manufacturer. This system shall be used for bonding of IFBs only </text>
<text top="196" left="216" width="289" height="14" font="27">with prior concurrence of EIL / Client / PMC. </text>
<text top="235" left="114" width="24" height="13" font="1"><b>5.0 </b></text>
<text top="235" left="192" width="66" height="13" font="1"><b>MIXING </b></text>
<text top="235" left="256" width="101" height="14" font="27">OF MORTAR </text>
<text top="273" left="114" width="25" height="13" font="1"><b>5.1 </b></text>
<text top="273" left="192" width="566" height="14" font="27">Each component of the mortar shall he mixed in proper proportions as per instructions of </text>
<text top="291" left="192" width="113" height="14" font="27">the manufacturer. </text>
<text top="330" left="114" width="24" height="14" font="27">5.2 </text>
<text top="330" left="191" width="566" height="14" font="27">Normally no conditioning or thinning of the mortar shall be carried out at site. In case same </text>
<text top="348" left="192" width="523" height="14" font="27">is required, it shall be carried out strictly as per the instructions of the manufacturer. </text>
<text top="387" left="114" width="24" height="14" font="27">5.3 </text>
<text top="386" left="192" width="566" height="14" font="27">Mortar shall preferably be mixed using a mechanical mortar mixer, unless otherwise </text>
<text top="404" left="191" width="118" height="14" font="27">approved the EIC. </text>
<text top="443" left="114" width="24" height="14" font="27">5.4 </text>
<text top="443" left="192" width="566" height="14" font="27">Mixed mortar shall be consumed within half an hour of mixing. Normally 150 kg of mortar </text>
<text top="461" left="192" width="333" height="14" font="27">is required per 1000 nos. 230x115x75 size firebricks. </text>
<text top="499" left="114" width="24" height="14" font="27">5.5 </text>
<text top="499" left="193" width="565" height="14" font="27">If water is required to be used, same shall be of potable quality. The water temperature shall </text>
<text top="517" left="192" width="342" height="14" font="27">be between 15 to 30 deg C, UON by the manufacturer. </text>
<text top="553" left="114" width="24" height="14" font="27">5.6 </text>
<text top="553" left="192" width="566" height="14" font="27">Mortar shall be mixed to a uniform trowelling / dipping consistency as applicable for </text>
<text top="571" left="192" width="127" height="14" font="27">installation method. </text>
<text top="607" left="114" width="25" height="13" font="1"><b>6.0 </b></text>
<text top="606" left="193" width="119" height="14" font="27">BRICK LAYING </text>
<text top="643" left="114" width="24" height="14" font="27">6.1 </text>
<text top="642" left="192" width="566" height="14" font="27">All brickwork shall be set out and built to the required dimensions as shown on the </text>
<text top="660" left="191" width="141" height="14" font="27">arrangement drawing. </text>
<text top="696" left="114" width="24" height="13" font="1"><b>6.2 </b></text>
<text top="696" left="192" width="567" height="14" font="27">The base course of brick shall rest directly on the floor plate and not on another refractory. </text>
<text top="714" left="192" width="242" height="14" font="27">The floor bricks shall not be mortared. </text>
<text top="750" left="114" width="25" height="14" font="27">6.3 </text>
<text top="750" left="192" width="567" height="14" font="27">Anchored bricks shall be drilled by electric drills for making holes in to the brick. Proper </text>
<text top="768" left="191" width="304" height="14" font="27">care shall be paid to make the exact size of hole. </text>
<text top="804" left="114" width="24" height="14" font="27">6.4 </text>
<text top="804" left="192" width="567" height="14" font="27">Tie back staples shall be provided as per drawing for anchoring the bricks. It shall be </text>
<text top="821" left="191" width="567" height="14" font="27">checked that sufficient space is available for movement of the staple to accommodate the </text>
<text top="839" left="192" width="227" height="14" font="27">vertical expansion of the brick wall. </text>
<text top="876" left="114" width="25" height="14" font="27">6.5 </text>
<text top="875" left="192" width="567" height="14" font="27">All joints in the bricks shall be mortared on the sides and ends, except at expansion joint </text>
<text top="894" left="192" width="63" height="14" font="27">locations. </text>
<text top="930" left="114" width="24" height="14" font="27">6.6 </text>
<text top="929" left="192" width="567" height="14" font="27">Mortar shall be smeared uniformly on the surface of the bricks with the help of trowels to </text>
<text top="947" left="192" width="567" height="14" font="27">provide smooth bedding of the bricks. The next brick should be dipped on one side and one </text>
<text top="965" left="192" width="567" height="14" font="27">end and placed upon the brick which has been covered with mortar. This will prevent from </text>
<text top="983" left="192" width="288" height="14" font="27">getting insufficient mortar between the joints. </text>
<text top="1019" left="115" width="24" height="14" font="27">6.7 </text>
<text top="1019" left="193" width="567" height="14" font="27">Mallet (light wooden hammer) shall be used for compacting the bricks to keep it in position </text>
<text top="1037" left="192" width="353" height="14" font="27">by removing the air voids and providing sound bonding. </text>
<text top="1073" left="115" width="24" height="14" font="27">6.8 </text>
<text top="1073" left="192" width="568" height="14" font="27">The thickness of mortar joints shall be consistent, as thin as possible, and to be not more </text>
<text top="1091" left="192" width="70" height="14" font="27">than 2mm. </text>
<text top="1142" left="585" width="174" height="10" font="0">Copyright EIL — All rights reserved </text>
<text top="1146" left="115" width="168" height="10" font="0">Format No 8-00-0001-F1 Rev. 0 </text>
</page>
