	<fontspec id="33" size="20" family="Times" color="#000000"/>
<text top="52" left="136" width="54" height="14" font="27">4oi  ei </text>
<text top="53" left="229" width="74" height="13" font="27">ENGINEERS </text>
<text top="64" left="110" width="95" height="18" font="33">4ige.il Elfieg </text>
<text top="66" left="229" width="98" height="14" font="27">INDIA LIMITED </text>
<text top="79" left="134" width="68" height="6" font="19">1.14WeleliTURelsi,FRIF.1.1 </text>
<text top="81" left="229" width="86" height="5" font="3">IA Govt of mad Unclefialongi </text>
<text top="45" left="350" width="228" height="12" font="1"><b>STANDARD SPECIFICATION FOR </b></text>
<text top="62" left="348" width="230" height="12" font="1"><b>INSTALLATION OF BRICK LINING </b></text>
<text top="78" left="395" width="135" height="12" font="1"><b>IN FIRED HEATERS </b></text>
<text top="45" left="606" width="178" height="10" font="0">STANDARD SPECIFICATION No. </text>
<text top="65" left="639" width="113" height="12" font="1"><b>6-17-0011 Rev. 2 </b></text>
<text top="83" left="664" width="64" height="10" font="0">Page 7 of 7  </text>
<text top="119" left="116" width="24" height="14" font="27">6.9 </text>
<text top="119" left="194" width="565" height="14" font="27">Periodically, the verticality and straightness of walls shall be checked using spirit levels, </text>
<text top="137" left="194" width="72" height="14" font="27">plumb, etc. </text>
<text top="173" left="116" width="32" height="14" font="30"><b>6.10 </b></text>
<text top="172" left="194" width="566" height="14" font="27">All walls shall be built up regularly, not leaving any part more than 1 meter lower than </text>
<text top="191" left="193" width="54" height="14" font="27">another. </text>
<text top="227" left="116" width="31" height="14" font="30"><b>6.11 </b></text>
<text top="226" left="194" width="565" height="14" font="27">Any walls if, left at different levels shall be stepped and sufficiently supported to avoid </text>
<text top="245" left="193" width="158" height="14" font="27">sagging in any direction. </text>
<text top="280" left="116" width="32" height="14" font="27">6.12 </text>
<text top="280" left="193" width="566" height="14" font="27">Any brick which gets cracked or broken during drilling or when anchor / staple is driven in, </text>
<text top="298" left="194" width="122" height="14" font="27">must be rejected. • </text>
<text top="334" left="116" width="32" height="14" font="27">6.13 </text>
<text top="334" left="194" width="566" height="14" font="27">Fire bricks shall be saw cut to size. They shall not be &#34;hammer&#34; cut or &#34;chipped&#34; into places. </text>
<text top="370" left="117" width="24" height="14" font="30"><b>7.0 </b></text>
<text top="370" left="194" width="155" height="14" font="30"><b>EXPANSION JOINTS </b></text>
<text top="406" left="117" width="24" height="14" font="27">7.1 </text>
<text top="405" left="195" width="566" height="14" font="27">Expansion joints shall be provided as given in the arrangement drawings. Width of the joints </text>
<text top="424" left="194" width="259" height="14" font="27">must not be less than the specified width. </text>
<text top="460" left="117" width="23" height="14" font="27">7.2 </text>
<text top="459" left="195" width="566" height="14" font="27">Expansion joints shall be provided in both vertical and horizontal directions of the walls, at </text>
<text top="478" left="194" width="410" height="14" font="27">wall edges and about burner tiles, doors and sleeved penetrations. </text>
<text top="514" left="117" width="24" height="14" font="27">7.3 </text>
<text top="514" left="194" width="253" height="14" font="27">Expansion joints shall be free of mortar. </text>
<text top="550" left="117" width="24" height="14" font="30"><b>7.4 </b></text>
<text top="549" left="194" width="568" height="14" font="27">Expansion joints shall be made by using plywood strips in the joints. Before insertion of </text>
<text top="567" left="194" width="537" height="14" font="27">plywood strips, it shall be greased for its easy removal after the setting of brick lining. </text>
<text top="603" left="117" width="24" height="14" font="30"><b>7.5 </b></text>
<text top="603" left="194" width="567" height="14" font="27">The expansion gap before filling shall be cleaned of any dust, debris or foreign material </text>
<text top="621" left="195" width="126" height="14" font="27">before gap packing. </text>
<text top="657" left="117" width="24" height="14" font="27">7.6 </text>
<text top="656" left="194" width="568" height="14" font="27">Suitable packing material e.g. ceramic fiber of 128 kg/m3, I 425°C grade shall be used for </text>
<text top="674" left="194" width="567" height="14" font="27">packing the expansion joints. The ceramic fiber shall be in blanket form and not loose </text>
<text top="692" left="194" width="567" height="14" font="27">material. The ceramic fiber shall be attached to one side of the expansion joint by heat </text>
<text top="710" left="194" width="363" height="14" font="27">resistant adhesive, to prevent dislodging during operation. </text>
<text top="747" left="117" width="24" height="14" font="27">7.7 </text>
<text top="746" left="195" width="566" height="14" font="27">If the bricks in a panel do not lay up to provide the width of expansion joints called for at </text>
<text top="764" left="194" width="567" height="14" font="27">the top of the panel, the top course must be saw cut to obtain the correct width of expansion </text>
<text top="782" left="193" width="37" height="14" font="27">joint. </text>
<text top="819" left="117" width="24" height="14" font="30"><b>7.8 </b></text>
<text top="818" left="194" width="423" height="14" font="27">Top course of all bricks shall be cut back in slope to retain packing. </text>
<text top="855" left="117" width="24" height="14" font="30"><b>7.9 </b></text>
<text top="854" left="194" width="567" height="14" font="27">Special shaped bricks may be required as indicated on arrangement drawing. It is essential </text>
<text top="871" left="195" width="567" height="14" font="27">that all mild steel parts shall be protected from furnace temperature and if any bricks require </text>
<text top="889" left="194" width="425" height="14" font="27">to be cut on site this may be done quite easily with an ordinary saw. </text>
